                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.61/2022: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-04T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 4, 1943—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>596. The British Ambassador on three occasions has asked me whether I had
                    received any instructions from my Government relative to the taking of action
                    jointly with him in regard to the Polish situation. <pb facs="0439" n="427"
                        xml:id="pg_427"/> He indicated that he had been informed that I would
                    receive such instructions and appeared disturbed at my reply in the
                    negative.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
